# MacArthur HAT – CAN interface configuration for NMEA2000
#
# Matches the MCP2518FD by its SPI bus path (spi0.1 = SPI0 CE1 = GPIO7)
# rather than by interface name, so the rule is stable if Venus OS renames
# the interface (e.g. to vecan0 or can8).
#
# LISTEN-ONLY mode: the MCP2518FD is configured as a passive bus observer.
# In normal CAN mode the node must ACK every received frame and may transmit
# active error flags.  On a live NMEA2000 bus this drove the rx error counter
# to the ERROR-PASSIVE threshold (128), causing the node to repeatedly enter
# the error-passive state and miss the majority of bus traffic.  Listen-only
# mode eliminates ACK transmission and error flag generation, dropping the
# rx error counter to 0 and restoring full frame reception.
#
# If you need to TRANSMIT on the NMEA2000 bus (e.g. for waypoint commands),
# remove "listen-only on" from the ip link command below and investigate the
# bus termination / transceiver hardware before enabling normal mode.

ACTION=="add", SUBSYSTEM=="net", KERNELS=="spi0.1", \
    RUN+="/sbin/ip link set %k up type can bitrate 250000 listen-only on restart-ms 100"
